rComments: Strong French accent but you get used to it. Humorous, but sometimes "I can't be bothered, go ask the TA" attitude. Tests were hard..

People didn't like his class because they thought it was too hard... but you just have to know how to study for his tests. He likes to test you on not just the theory but HOW you arrive to the theory, meaning a lot of his questions were focused on the processes/equations of making the lines for the graphs and not just being able to use the graph it
Often doesn't align tests with textbooks. But overall, I worked so hard for his class but learned so much.  His teaching isn't always the clearest, but his notes are superb and he is funny and nice.
hard hard hard tests! Terrible teacher
